This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of retinal vessels from retinal fundus images using image processing techniques. It may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves the extraction of relevant information from medical images. Additionally, it may be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of visual data. The use of fuzzy C-mean classification and morphological operations suggests that it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of anisotropic diffusion filtering and weighted scaling suggests that it may be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
